The article is a transcript of a press briefing by Secretary of State Hillary Clinton and Press Secretary Robert Gibbs. They discuss Clinton's meetings with President Karzai and President Zardari, as well as the progress being made in the relationship between Afghanistan and Pakistan. They also talk about the importance of cooperation between the two countries in addressing the common threat of terrorism. Clinton mentions specific commitments made in areas such as agriculture and economic development. The briefing also touches on other topics such as the upcoming Supreme Court nomination and the situation in Iraq.